---
description: WCAG-oriented accessibility requirements for public landing page changes
alwaysApply: false
globs:
  - "src/**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,css,scss,html}"
---

accessibility:
- Target WCAG 2.2 AA for public journeys.
- Use one meaningful `h1`; preserve logical heading order.
- Use native controls and landmarks before ARIA.
- Every interactive element must work with keyboard only.
- Focus must be visible and must not be hidden by sticky UI.
- Links and buttons require descriptive accessible names.
- Images require meaningful alt text or empty alt when decorative.
- Form fields require persistent labels, instructions, error association, and recovery guidance.
- Do not encode meaning by color alone.
- Validate text contrast and non-text contrast.
- Touch targets must be comfortable on mobile.
- Avoid autoplay, flashing, and motion that cannot be reduced.
- Test at 200% zoom and with narrow viewports.
